# The Graph Studio Deploy Keys
# Get your deploy key from https://thegraph.com/studio/

# ========================================
# Option 1: Single Key (Recommended)
# ========================================
# Use this if you're managing with one Graph Studio account
# Usage: pnpm auth
GRAPH_STUDIO_DEPLOY_KEY=your-deploy-key-here

# ========================================
# Option 2: Network-specific Keys (For advanced use cases)
# ========================================
# Use these if you have separate Graph Studio projects per network
# Usage: pnpm auth:amoy or pnpm auth:polygon

# Amoy testnet deploy key (Polygon zkEVM)
AMOY_DEPLOY_KEY=your-amoy-deploy-key-here

# Polygon mainnet deploy key
POLYGON_DEPLOY_KEY=your-polygon-deploy-key-here

# ========================================
# Notes:
# ========================================
# - You can use EITHER Option 1 OR Option 2, or both
# - If using Option 1 (single key), you only need to set GRAPH_STUDIO_DEPLOY_KEY
# - If using Option 2 (network keys), set AMOY_DEPLOY_KEY and/or POLYGON_DEPLOY_KEY
# - Network-specific keys (Option 2) take precedence over single key (Option 1)
# - ⚠️ WARNING: Polygon mainnet deployments incur real costs. Use testnet (Amoy) for testing.
